The article discusses the importance of Human Rights Day and Human Rights Week, which commemorate the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. The United States reaffirms its commitment to upholding human rights and defending fundamental freedoms globally. The article highlights the country's efforts to promote equal rights for women, LGBTQI+ individuals, and underserved communities, as well as its work to address systemic racism and expand accessibility for people with disabilities. The Universal Declaration of Human Rights is seen as a crucial foundation for tackling global challenges and promoting the enjoyment of all human rights. President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaims December 10, 2023, as Human Rights Day and the week beginning December 10, 2023, as Human Rights Week, calling upon the people of the United States to observe these occasions.